OL,3,CChurch leadership say Bishop of
OL,4,CLiverpool 'will need to step aside'
OL,6,FThe allegations, which the Bishop John
OL,7,FPerumbalath denies, allege that he
OL,8,Fsexually assaulted a senior
OL,9,Fclergywoman in Essex on separate
OL,10,Foccasions between 2019 and 2023 -
OL,11,Fafter two women separately made
OL,12,Fdisclosures to victims' advocate
OL,13,FAndrew Graystone.
OL,15,FWriting to the Archbishop of York
OL,16,FStephen Cottrell, a number of senior
OL,17,Fleaders of the Diocese of Liverpool
OL,18,Fsaid that they had listened to their
OL,19,Fclergy, congregations, and staff, and
OL,20,Fhad concluded that the Bishop's
OL,21,Fposition is "currently untenable".
