OL,3,CChurch leadership say Bishop of
OL,4,CLiverpool 'will need to step aside'
OL,6,FA statement, signed by six members of
OL,7,Fthe senior leadership of the Diocese
OL,8,Fof Liverpool, says: "Having listened
OL,9,Fto clergy, congregations and staff at
OL,10,Fthe diocesan offices and the
OL,11,Fcathedral, it is with deep regret that
OL,12,Fthe senior leadership of the Diocese
OL,13,Fof Liverpool feel that the position of
OL,14,Fthe Rt Revd Dr John Perumbalath is
OL,15,Fcurrently untenable.
OL,17,F"We believe that the allegations made
OL,18,Fby the female bishop need to be fully
OL,19,Fand properly investigated.
